es contents  early life  career  personal life  professional history  references  external links early lifeedit terry j lundgren was born in  and received a bachelors degree from the university of arizona in  careeredit through his career at federatedmacys lundgren is credited with being an innovator in merchandising branding and localization he was instrumental in developing the companys private brands of merchandise and led the  merger of federated department stores inc and may department stores inc creating one of the largest retailers in the world with more than  us stores and  net sales of us billion like all retailers macys inc saw declining sales in  amid deterioration of the us economy in fiscal  through january  samestore sales declined by  at macys inc in this environment however macys inc has outperformed virtually every major competitor macys is seeing positive early results from my macys a localization initiative launched by lundgren in spring  to tailor a portion of every stores assortment to local tastes and color the company reported that of its top  bestperforming geographic markets in the key holiday selling month of december   were my macys pilot districts the my macys organizational model is being rolled out across the us in  as reported in macys incs proxy statement filed in april  lundgrens total compensation in  declined by  to  million reflecting lower sales and profitability in a weak economy his compensation included  million in salary  under the nonequity incentive plan and  in various other compensation the remainder was the value of stock optionscitation needed lundgrens salary and the composition of the macys board of directors was cited by republican presidential candidate donald trump as an example of an overcompensated chief executive officer in a september  television interview trump stated that the high salaries paid to ceos was often a joke and a disgrace trump cited macys inc as an example lundgren has been awarded numerous honors in  he received the gold medal award from the national retail federation considered the retailing industrys preeminent honor in spring  he was presented with carnegie halls third annual medal of excellence for outstanding philanthropic leadership in the arts the gala held in lundgrens honor raised  million for carnegie hall lundgren is very active in the community he has been appointed commissioner on womens economic development by the mayor of new york also on behalf of nyc mayor michael r bloomberg he served as one of the industry chairs of fashionnyc which looked at the future of nycs fashion industry and made recommendations for actionable steps the nyc government could take to promote nycs fashion industry he has been presented with several business recognition awards and has served as dinner chairman or as honoree for numerous retail industry organizations and charities including the fresh air fund american jewish council breast cancer awareness now legal defense parsons school and the ovarian cancer society lundgren currently serves on the boards of carnegie hall the new york city partnership and united way of new york city as well as participating in numerous other charitable and civic effortscitation needed lundgren is chairman of the national minority supplier development council he is on the membership committee of the economic club of new york and is involved with the new york city principal for a day program personal lifeedit born in long beach california lundgren was one of six children after graduating college he joined federated and rose quickly to lead the upscale specialty bullocks wilshire division in los angeles at age  lundgren was married to nancy cross until their divorce he has two daughters from this marriage lundgren married tina stephan in citation needed lundgren is also the namesake of the terry j lundgren center for retailing at the university of arizona where he is also an alumnus having graduated in  with a bachelors degree in  lundgren was awarded an honorary doctorate and delivered the universitys commencement address professional historyedit federated department stores bullocks division – bullocks wilshire – president neiman marcus – evp then chairmanceo federated merchandising group  chairmanceo macys inc called federated department stores inc prior to june   – president and chief merchandising officer – president and chief operating officer – chairman president and ceo present executive  referencesedit  terry j lundgren — biography  learning the value of hard work referenceforbusinesscom retrieved    keynotes — hbs retail and luxury goods conference wwwhbsrlgconferencecom retrieved    bustillo miguel  february  retailers stop making sales forecasts the wall street journal   rosenbloom stephanie  macy’s cuts dividend and  jobs the new york times   hughes krista  september  trump says high pay for ceos is a joke and disgraceful reuters   gatti mike a long history of recognizing retails best nrfcom retrieved  april    carnegie hall medal of excellence gala honoring terry j lundgren raises  million pr newswire april   retrieved may     strauss steven kristy sundjaja eric johnson meghana gandhi victor wong jennifer yoo  fashionnyc nycedc   emcee  honorees  national minority supplier development council national minority supplier development council retrieved    trustees  officers  the economic club of new york wwweconclubnyorg retrieved    macys terry j lundgren to be honored at annual fit gala  norton school family and consumer sciences calsarizonaedu retrieved    business leaders macy’s terry lundgren fox business retrieved  june    brooke kim alumnus names ua center for retailing and consumer sciences the university of arizona retrieved  june   external linksedit biography on macysinccom v t e macys inc bloomingdales bluemercury macys key people terry j lundgren fred lazarus jr simon lazarus rowland hussey macy isidor straus nathan straus events glamorama macys great tree macys thanksgiving