g rolled out across the us in  as reported in macys incs proxy statement filed in april  lundgrens total compensation in  declined by  to  million reflecting lower sales and profitability in a weak economy his compensation included  million in salary  under the nonequity incentive plan and  in various other compensation the remainder was the value of stock optionscitation needed lundgrens salary and the composition of the macys board of directors was cited by republican presidential candidate donald trump as an example of an overcompensated chief executive officer in a september  television interview trump stated that the high salaries paid to ceos was often a joke and a disgrace trump cited macys inc as an example lundgren has been awarded numerous honors in  he received the gold medal award from the national retail federation considered the retailing industrys preeminent honor in spring  he was presented with carnegie halls third annual medal of excellence for outstanding philanthropic leadership in the arts the gala held in lundgrens honor raised  million for carnegie hall lundgren is very active in the community he has been appointed commissioner on womens economic development by the mayor of new york also on behalf of nyc mayor michael r bloomberg he served as one of the industry chairs of fashionnyc which looked at the future of nycs fashion industry and made recommendations for actionable steps the nyc government could take to promote nycs fashion industry he has been presented with several business recognition awards and has served as dinner chairman or as honoree for numerous retail industry organizations and charities including the fresh air fund american jewish council breast cancer awareness now legal defense parsons school and the ovarian cancer society lundgren currently serves on the boards of carnegie hall the new york city partnership and united way of new york city as well as participating in numerous other charitable and civic effortscitation needed lundgren is chairman of the national minority supplier development council he is on the membership committee of the economic club of new york and is involved with the new york city principal for a day program personal lifeedit born in long beach california lundgren was one of six children after graduating college he joined federated and rose quickly to lead the upscale specialty bullocks wilshire division in los angeles at age  lundgren was married to nancy cross until their divorce he has two daughters from this marriage lundgren married tina stephan in citation needed lundgren is also the namesake of the terry j lundgren center for retailing at the university of arizona where he is also an alumnus having graduated in  with a bachelors degree in  lundgren was awarded an honorary doctorate and delivered the universitys commencement address professional historyedit federated department stores bullocks division – bullocks wilshire – president neiman marcus – evp then chairmanceo federated merchandising group  chairmanceo macys inc called federated department stores inc prior to june   – president and chief merchandising officer – president and chief operating officer – chairman president and ceo present executive  referencesedit  terry j lundgren — biography  learning the value of hard work referenceforbusinesscom retrieved    keynotes — hbs retail and luxury goods conference wwwhbsrlgconferencecom retrieved    bustillo miguel  february  retailers stop making sales forecasts the wall street journal   rosenbloom stephanie  macy’s cuts dividend and  jobs the new york times   hughes krista  september  trump says high pay for ceos is a joke and disgraceful reuters   gatti mike a long history of recognizing retails best nrfcom retrieved  april    carnegie hall medal of excellence gala honoring terry j lundgren raises  million pr newswire april   retrieved may     strauss steven kristy sundjaja eric johnson meghana gandhi victor wong jennifer yoo  fashionnyc nycedc   emc